The Hessian of a scalar field $f$ is the matrix that contains all its  second-order partial derivative information.

$\bold{H}(f) = \begin{bmatrix}
f_{xx} & f_{xy} \\ \\
f_{yx} & f_{yy}
\end{bmatrix}$

Because the order of mixed partial derivatives often doesn't matter, the bottom left and top right entries of the Hessian are usually the same.

